        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Additionally, I think there are two ways to achieve this:\n1. Server only sends a `restart` UI event. Client then invokes `:qall` on server, waits for it to end, and then starts a new server. However, there may be server autocommands that block the restart and/or produce more UI events.\n2. Server does `:qall` itself and only sends `restart` UI event when definitely exiting (after triggering autocommands). Client just needs to start a new server. However, if the client hasn't implemented the `restart` UI event, `:restart` will be equivalent to `:qall` instead of no-op.",
