            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Perhaps `v:progpath` and `v:argv` should be included in the `restart` UI event?\n\nyeah, I think ~~the UI event~~ (edit: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34367 suggests to do it on the server instead) will need to be able to send `:restart [args]` also, like: \n\n    :restart +qall\n    :restart +qall set foo=bar\n\n> Server does `:qall` itself and only sends `restart` UI event when definitely exiting (after triggering autocommands). Client just needs to start a new server. However, if the client hasn't implemented the `restart` UI event, `:restart` will be equivalent to `:qall` instead of no-op.\n\nThat sounds like a great approach.",
